Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.08,0:01:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and second, when we think about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.37,0:01:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility it's really making
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.27,0:01:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,technology usable by everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.37,0:01:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of whatever their
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.54,0:01:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,unique needs might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.40,0:01:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At Apple, we approach this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.78,0:01:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,problem by examining four major
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.11,0:01:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,classes of user ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.52,0:01:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,cognitive, motor, vision and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.82,0:01:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.06,0:01:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Cognitive encompasses conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.79,0:01:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,like dyslexia or autism.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.19,0:01:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Motor examines the way in which
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.17,0:01:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,a user physically interacts with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the system, whether they need
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.56,0:01:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,special accommodations for a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.84,0:01:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,condition like Parkinson's or
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.51,0:01:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,cerebral palsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.91,0:01:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Vision which encompasses a range
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.98,0:01:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of visionability from those with
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.97,0:01:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,low vision conditions to those
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.02,0:01:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,who are completely blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.65,0:01:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally hearing which like
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.02,0:01:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,vision encompasses a spectrum of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.06,0:02:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,hearing ability from those who
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.15,0:02:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,are hard of hearing to those
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.95,0:02:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that are completely deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.78,0:02:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Worldwide there are over a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.18,0:02:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,billion people who have some
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.76,0:02:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,form of disability that fit into
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.24,0:02:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,one of those categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.43,0:02:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Put another way, one in seven,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.93,0:02:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,one in seven people have a form
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.63,0:02:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of disability which means that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.89,0:02:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to have and already
