Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.90,0:08:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,description.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.31,0:08:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We look for things like the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.74,0:08:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,number of faces within an image,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.85,0:08:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,what expressions are they
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.91,0:08:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,making, what's the overall scene
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.07,0:08:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of that image, and what's its
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.58,0:08:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,blurriness or brightness level.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a description for an image
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.00,0:08:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,like this one might sound like
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.64,0:08:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,>> One face, one smiling,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.70,0:08:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,nightclub, blurry, bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.87,0:08:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Now if you're a developer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,who's already gone through and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.41,0:08:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,done your due diligence of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.77,0:08:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,labeling all your images don't
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.32,0:08:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,worry we're not just going to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.86,0:08:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,hijack that description from
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.44,0:08:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.27,0:08:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, if a user wants to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.42,0:08:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the description that we
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.49,0:09:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,ourselves have generated that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.15,0:09:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all they need to do is a single
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.46,0:09:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,three-finger tap on the image
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.22,0:09:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and they'll hear our
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.98,0:09:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,description.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.80,0:09:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have large texts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.60,0:09:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this year our team did an
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.98,0:09:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,audit of the large text
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.57,0:09:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,experience systemwide with a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.23,0:09:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,real focus on the experience of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.96,0:09:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,those users who use our largest
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.93,0:09:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility text sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.82,0:09:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And we worked with teams across
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.76,0:09:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Apple to really, really improve
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.60,0:09:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,this experience, which also
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.18,0:09:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,includes some new APIs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.16,0:09:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there's a lot that I could
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.35,0:09:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,say about this feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.13,0:09:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, there's so much that I
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.78,0:09:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,could say about this feature
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.65,0:09:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a whole other session
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.84,0:09:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated just to dynamic type
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.72,0:09:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it's called Building Apps with
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.09,0:09:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Dynamic Type.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's going to be in the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.42,0:09:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,executive ballroom Friday at
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.35,0:09:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,1:50 and I highly, highly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.74,0:09:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,recommend that you attend to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.04,0:09:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,figure out how to best adapt
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.59,0:09:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,your own apps for dynamic type
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.11,0:09:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in iOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.36,0:10:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there are two other sessions
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.07,0:10:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,up here that I'd like to point
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.29,0:10:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,out that also contain relevant
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.86,0:10:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,information about dynamic type.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.18,0:10:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The first Design for Everyone is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.50,0:10:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a session that focuses on the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,design of accessibility, but
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.94,0:10:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,will also contain a portion that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.96,0:10:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,will cover dynamic type,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.76,0:10:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,including some of the rationale
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.66,0:10:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,behind decisions that we made
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.61,0:10:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,when adapting the layouts for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.13,0:10:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,large text and design
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.85,0:10:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,considerations that you yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.24,0:10:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,should make when designing your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.80,0:10:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,own apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And second, Auto Layout
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Techniques in Interface Builder
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.79,0:10:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,will have a portion dedicated to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.34,0:10:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,adapting your layouts that are
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,built with interface builder for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.12,0:10:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic type.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.52,0:10:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I hope to see you all at
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,these sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.87,0:10:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Moving on, we have the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.83,0:10:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.29,0:10:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a feature built for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.83,0:10:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,macOS for users who have enough
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.47,0:10:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,dexterity to use a trackpad, but
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.19,0:11:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,can't necessarily use a physical
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.21,0:11:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,keyboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.91,0:11:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an onscreen keyboard that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.82,0:11:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,has things like system controls
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.21,0:11:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and a predictive text bar and is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.79,0:11:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,fully customizable, which means
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.66,0:11:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that if I have certain actions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.76,0:11:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that I do on a daily basis that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.95,0:11:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to create a custom panel
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.45,0:11:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,for so I just have to click it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.21,0:11:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,once and it'll initiate that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.64,0:11:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,action then I can create those
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.24,0:11:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,panels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.41,0:11:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance if I email my
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.47,0:11:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,manager every day I may create a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.43,0:11:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,custom panel that opens mail,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.03,0:11:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,composes an email, and adds her
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.20,0:11:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,address in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.73,0:11:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have Type to Siri, so
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.33,0:11:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,like the title suggests this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.93,0:11:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,feature allows you to interact
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.50,0:11:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,with Siri via text input like
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.80,0:11:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you would via speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.89,0:11:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're really excited about
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.40,0:11:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,this because it's going to open
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.69,0:11:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,up Siri to a class of users who
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.43,0:11:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,are unable to use it before,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.11,0:11:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,those who are nonverbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.46,0:12:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, we have Smart Invert
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.28,0:12:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.84,0:12:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, previously on iOS if you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.53,0:12:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,enabled the invert colors
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.82,0:12:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,feature it would invert all the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.76,0:12:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,content of your device
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.44,0:12:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of what kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,content it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.19,0:12:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But this year we're introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.35,0:12:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Smart Invert Colors, which looks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.70,0:12:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,at specific kinds of content
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.22,0:12:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,like graphics or images and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.16,0:12:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't invert them so that you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.51,0:12:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,can see the content as it was
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.97,0:12:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,actually meant to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.44,0:12:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd actually like to do a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.89,0:12:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,demo of that feature for you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.90,0:12:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.09,0:12:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I have my device here and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.92,0:12:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to enable Smart Invert
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.51,0:12:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.25,0:12:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now as you can see, the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.78,0:12:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,wallpaper wasn't inverted nor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.66,0:12:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,were all of the app icons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.37,0:12:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I go into my Photos app,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.55,0:12:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see that I still have the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.88,0:13:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,dark UI that is important for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.36,0:13:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,users who use invert colors that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.59,0:13:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,have certain low-vision
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.49,0:13:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions where a white UI
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.12,0:13:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,makes the display too difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.50,0:13:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at for prolonged periods
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.82,0:13:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.63,0:13:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I can still see my photos as
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.84,0:13:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,they originally were.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.45,0:13:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if I go to an app like Clock
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which already had a dark UI
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.32,0:13:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll also notice that we
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.94,0:13:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't inverted that UI to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.73,0:13:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the dark look around that is so
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.10,0:13:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,important to our invert colors
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.31,0:13:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.14,0:13:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's just a very basic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.19,0:13:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,overview of that feature and I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.49,0:13:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,highly recommend that you check
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it out yourself and see how it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.04,0:13:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,plays around with your own apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.18,0:13:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I'd like to pivot into
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.91,0:13:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about the experience of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.10,0:13:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you as a developer and how you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.09,0:13:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that all of your work
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.13,0:13:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,works with all the things that I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.37,0:13:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,just covered, as well as all of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.44,0:13:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,our old features.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.88,0:13:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And that really begins by
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.83,0:14:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,auditing your app for
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.40,0:14:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.12,0:14:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when we're starting an audit
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.79,0:14:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing you're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.63,0:14:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,want to do is enable an
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.47,0:14:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible technology like
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.82,0:14:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Voiceover or Switch Control and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.09,0:14:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,see what the experience is like
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.46,0:14:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for a Voiceover user.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to do that we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.33,0:14:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,tap on General Accessibility and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.09,0:14:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,go down to this accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.64,0:14:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,shortcut page and add VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.82,0:14:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to our shortcut.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.54,0:14:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What this does is that now
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.50,0:14:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever I triple click the Home
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.09,0:14:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,button VoiceOver will turn on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.50,0:14:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I have VoiceOver on
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.92,0:14:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,already it will turn VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.21,0:14:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,off so I can quickly cycle
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.48,0:14:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,between the two as I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,through my app.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.24,0:14:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that we have VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.86,0:14:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.25,0:14:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to Home out of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.21,0:14:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,settings and go to the app that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.31,0:14:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to audit and just start
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.01,0:14:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,playing around to see what the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,experience is like for a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.00,0:15:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver user.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.18,0:15:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Are all the things that I would
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.36,0:15:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,expect to be visible visible?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the things that I would not
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.08,0:15:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,want to be visible to a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.83,0:15:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver user not visible to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.02,0:15:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.24,0:15:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Does every interaction with the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.73,0:15:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,interface have some sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,corollary that a VoiceOver user
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.42,0:15:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,can take advantage of?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.67,0:15:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And does the UI itself make
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.27,0:15:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,sense, does the flow make sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.87,0:15:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As well are elements properly
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.24,0:15:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,labeled?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.61,0:15:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, I would expect
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.49,0:15:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,this button that's an upload
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.87,0:15:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,button to be labeled upload tell
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.48,0:15:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,me it has three votes currently
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.05,0:15:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it's a button.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.31,0:15:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have a tool called the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.75,0:15:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Accessibility Inspector that can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.66,0:15:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,also be used for auditing your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.31,0:15:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,apps.
