Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.32,0:23:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,this UI with by just feeling my
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.14,0:23:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,finger around the screen it's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.10,0:23:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,much harder to find that tiny
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.02,0:23:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,play button to play the movie
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.52,0:23:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,than it is to find that big
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.85,0:23:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,area.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.63,0:23:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have accessibilityLabel
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.64,0:23:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,which describes what an element
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.36,0:23:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.66,0:23:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example with our memory
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.10,0:23:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,view it's a memory and its title
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.89,0:23:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is February 18th, 2017.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.87,0:23:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that seems like a reasonable
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.81,0:23:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,label.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.75,0:23:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But now because we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.83,0:23:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,be treating it like a button you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.98,0:23:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,might wonder why we don't add
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.36,0:24:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the word button into our label
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.41,0:24:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's because of this next
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.88,0:24:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,property, accessibilityTraits.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.15,0:24:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This indicates to VoiceOver what
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.36,0:24:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,category an element fits into.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.09,0:24:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.07,0:24:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,set our memory view
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.18,0:24:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityTraits to include
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.97,0:24:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the button trait so that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.14,0:24:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver knows to treat it like
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.50,0:24:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a button.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.74,0:24:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This also means that when it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.84,0:24:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,reads the description for the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.06,0:24:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,item it's going to say button at
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.55,0:24:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of that so that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.91,0:24:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,knows what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.23,0:24:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now traits are also important
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.66,0:24:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,for two more reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.18,0:24:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,One, they can afford certain UI
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.97,0:24:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,behaviors which you'll see you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.68,0:24:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,later in the presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.51,0:24:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And two, there's mechanisms for
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.51,0:24:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,users to navigate the interface
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.19,0:24:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,based on specific kinds of items
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.18,0:24:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that will be surfaced based on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.77,0:24:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what traits are associated with
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.83,0:24:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.17,0:24:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have accessibilityValue
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.15,0:24:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which is for elements that have
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.21,0:24:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,some form of state.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.99,0:25:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance if we're in our
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.30,0:25:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,memory video and we're editing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.35,0:25:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a scrubber along the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.48,0:25:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom that allows me to scrub
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.60,0:25:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,through the whole video.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.65,0:25:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the current valve of that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.63,0:25:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,item is the second that I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.70,0:25:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,focused on of the elapsed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.19,0:25:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds that have already
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.20,0:25:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.25,0:25:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I can set its accessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.59,0:25:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,value to be that elapsed number
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.00,0:25:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of seconds that I'm currently
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.06,0:25:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.56,0:25:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, we have
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.18,0:25:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityHint.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.76,0:25:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is meant to be a more
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.26,0:25:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,longform description of how to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.45,0:25:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,interact with an element, what
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.03,0:25:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it does or what it's meant for.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.14,0:25:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You can think of this as being a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.27,0:25:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,property that allows you to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.19,0:25:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,describe to a user that's new to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.94,0:25:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,your interface and help them
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.06,0:25:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,learn how to use your interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.75,0:25:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's important that you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.56,0:25:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,never put critical information
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.32,0:25:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to whoever's using it in a hint
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.62,0:25:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because hints can actually be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.86,0:25:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,disabled to keep VoiceOver from
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.81,0:26:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,being too verbose for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.17,0:26:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced users.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.12,0:26:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, going a little further.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.90,0:26:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,New this year we have attributed
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.06,0:26:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,versions of label, value and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.60,0:26:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.59,0:26:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And what these allow you to do
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.46,0:26:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is pass through specific keys to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.77,0:26:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,tweak the way in which VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.88,0:26:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,speaks a string.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.82,0:26:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example if I have a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.94,0:26:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,string that I know I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.61,0:26:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,speak -- that's in a different
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.67,0:26:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,language and should be spoken
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.72,0:26:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with a different voice
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.92,0:26:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,synthesizer specific to that
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.42,0:26:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,language then I can use the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.55,0:26:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,UIAccessibilitySpeech
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.08,0:26:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,AttributeLanguage key and pass
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.75,0:26:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the correct language code so
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.85,0:26:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that when VoiceOver speaks it,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.74,0:26:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it speaks it with say in this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.56,0:26:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,example, the French synthesizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.52,0:26:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now as well let's say I had an
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.59,0:26:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,announcement that I wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.74,0:26:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,post and speak, but I felt like
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.11,0:26:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that announcement isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.84,0:27:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,important enough to interrupt
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.36,0:27:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever current speech is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.44,0:27:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.60,0:27:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well in this case I can use an
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.87,0:27:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,attributed string with the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.53,0:27:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,UIAccessibilitySpeech
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.09,0:27:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,AttributeQueueAnnouncement that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.28,0:27:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,will queue the speech behind
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.89,0:27:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever existing speech is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.03,0:27:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,already there so that it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.17,0:27:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,spoken whatever VoiceOver was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.10,0:27:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,already speaking is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.04,0:27:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, new this year we have the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.05,0:27:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,concept of containers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.52,0:27:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So previously, when a VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.41,0:27:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,user would swipe into a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.81,0:27:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,container of some kind they
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.98,0:27:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't really get an
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.63,0:27:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,indication of what kind of thing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.01,0:27:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they were swiping into, what
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.97,0:27:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,does those content actually even
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.52,0:27:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.07,0:27:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're introducing
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.97,0:27:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityContainerType where
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.05,0:27:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you can define this and there
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.04,0:27:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,are several different kinds of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.51,0:27:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,containers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.36,0:27:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest one there is
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.02,0:27:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,dataTable which actually
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.82,0:27:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,requires conformance to the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.29,0:27:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility container
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.58,0:27:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,dataTable protocol and improves
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.35,0:27:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the way in which a VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.76,0:27:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,user can navigate through your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.13,0:28:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,dataTable and understand where
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.66,0:28:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.96,0:28:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everything that I just
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.00,0:28:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,covered there applies to views
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.24,0:28:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would use through UIKit
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.35,0:28:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.70,0:28:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if your controls exist
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.81,0:28:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,out of UIKit, you have some sort
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.74,0:28:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of non-view element that perhaps
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.03,0:28:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you've drawn using core
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.31,0:28:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,graphics.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.74,0:28:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well in that case we still need
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.35,0:28:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to surface those controls to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.66,0:28:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver and so we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.75,0:28:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,use UI accessibilityElement to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.47,0:28:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,represent logical accessible
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.77,0:28:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,regions of the screen to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.01,0:28:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,basically stand in for those
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.01,0:28:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,controls.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.20,0:28:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, UI accessibilityElement you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.66,0:28:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,set all the properties that I
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.70,0:28:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,covered before on it like you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.56,0:28:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,would on any other view and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.72,0:28:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,initialized with an
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.67,0:28:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility container that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.47,0:28:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the view that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.41,0:28:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,contained in.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.41,0:28:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you override on the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.62,0:28:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,container the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.45,0:28:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityElements protocol
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.99,0:29:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,which tells VoiceOver what sub
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.86,0:29:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,elements within a view are the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.52,0:29:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,accessible elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.32,0:29:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the order in which elements
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.76,0:29:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,are returned in this array is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.72,0:29:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the order in which VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.34,0:29:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,will swipe through them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.07,0:29:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So that seems like a great
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.96,0:29:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,candidate for combining those
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.41,0:29:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,profile elements into a single
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.97,0:29:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,element.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.92,0:29:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's come back over to our
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.58,0:29:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,sample app and take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.21,0:29:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,implementing some of these
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.01,0:29:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,basics.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.25,0:29:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so I have -- I'm in my
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.11,0:29:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,home view controller which is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.21,0:29:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the main screen I'm on and the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.67,0:29:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,first I want to do is fix the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.71,0:29:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,labels for those buttons that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.33,0:29:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,are up on the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.05,0:30:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for the add button I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.87,0:30:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to say new post because it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.22,0:30:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,creates a new post.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.86,0:30:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The notifications button I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.00,0:30:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,going to set its label to be
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.86,0:30:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications and its value to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.51,0:30:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,be my current number of unread
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.27,0:30:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.48,0:30:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the settings button I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.19,0:30:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,going to set to be settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.05,0:30:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm going to go take care of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.93,0:30:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,those other unlabeled buttons
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.98,0:30:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that were my upload and download
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.43,0:30:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.54,0:30:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for my approved button I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.28,0:30:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,going to set its label to be up
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.59,0:30:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,vote and for my disapprove
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.26,0:30:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,button down vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.51,0:30:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I need to also remember to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.22,0:30:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,change the accessibility value
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.18,0:30:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of these buttons whenever my
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.24,0:30:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,number of approves or number of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.56,0:30:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,disapproves changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.15,0:30:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when I come into here I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.54,0:30:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,going to make a switch statement
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.26,0:30:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,based on number of approves.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.82,0:30:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's one I'm going to say
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.68,0:30:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the number of approves vote
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.66,0:30:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,or when it's more than one I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.01,0:30:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,going to day number of approves
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.09,0:30:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.89,0:31:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to do the same
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.88,0:31:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.60,0:31:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,For the disapprove.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.72,0:31:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's go to the star view
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.99,0:31:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which was previously
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.31,0:31:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,inaccessible and we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.61,0:31:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,make that an accessible element.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.05,0:31:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing that we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.77,0:31:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to do is override
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.71,0:31:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,isAccessibilityElement to return
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.58,0:31:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,true so that VoiceOver knows
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.30,0:31:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is an element it
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.27,0:31:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,should focus on.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.25,0:31:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to set its label to be
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.45,0:31:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,star rating because that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.20,0:31:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.19,0:31:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And then for its value based on
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.82,0:31:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of stars we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.89,0:31:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to return either no rating, one
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.33,0:31:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,star or the current number of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.54,0:31:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.17,0:31:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So now let's come back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.81,0:31:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,home view controller where we
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.66,0:31:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,had those labels that we wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.98,0:31:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to join together to be a single
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.81,0:32:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,element that acted like a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.12,0:32:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.88,0:32:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what we're going to do for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.47,0:32:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that is a couple things.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.67,0:32:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to create a UI
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.03,0:32:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityElement the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.80,0:32:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,container of which is the header
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.15,0:32:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,view and then we're going to set
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.50,0:32:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,its label to be my profile name,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.01,0:32:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,its value to be my number of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.27,0:32:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,open posts, and its traits to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.75,0:32:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,include the button traits so the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.19,0:32:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,user knows that they can
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.37,0:32:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,interact with it like a button.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.22,0:32:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I'm going to find its
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.30,0:32:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,frame and set this property
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.05,0:32:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityFrame
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.17,0:32:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,InContainerSpace.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.56,0:32:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is important because
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.58,0:32:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for a couple reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.47,0:32:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's telling VoiceOver where the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.99,0:32:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,element is onscreen and the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.13,0:32:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinate space of its
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.34,0:32:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,container which is used to draw
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.97,0:32:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the bounding box, as well as
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.74,0:32:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,when a VoiceOver user is feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.25,0:32:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,around the screen for elements
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.11,0:32:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's using this property to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.29,0:32:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,detect whether or not an element
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.87,0:32:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can be found underneath their
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.20,0:32:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.68,0:33:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, on our header view,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.88,0:33:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to set our
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.71,0:33:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityElements to contain
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.27,0:33:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,our new element plus those three
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.85,0:33:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons that we had already.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.56,0:33:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Last but not least, I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.31,0:33:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,come to the switch cell and make
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.08,0:33:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,this the whole cell an
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.41,0:33:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility element and for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.28,0:33:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,its value based on whether or
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.21,0:33:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,not the switch is currently on
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.81,0:33:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to say on or off as
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.36,0:33:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,its accessibility value.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.95,0:33:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let me build that to my
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.25,0:33:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,device.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.05,0:33:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,>> VoiceOver on mail, no unread
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.11,0:33:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,emails.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.82,0:33:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Double tap to open.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.05,0:33:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, give me one sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.75,0:33:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Alert, selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.06,0:34:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay well I have thankfully a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.48,0:34:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,premade version of this that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.76,0:34:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,actually already has the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.80,0:34:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibility in it so we're
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.56,0:34:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,going to launch that and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.19,0:34:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,going to turn on VoiceOver.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.99,0:34:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,>> VoiceOver on Pre-Poster EX
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.94,0:34:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Tom McNeil two open posts
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.69,0:34:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.30,0:34:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And the first thing that you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.43,0:34:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,see is that I have joined those
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.76,0:34:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,elements together and that it's
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.28,0:34:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,spoken that it's a button.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.16,0:34:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Tap the add button,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.07,0:34:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications three, button
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.44,0:34:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,settings button.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.45,0:34:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All those buttons have proper
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.72,0:34:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,labels.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.12,0:34:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Down vote two button, up vote
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.07,0:34:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,three button.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.98,0:34:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Those have proper labels as
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.42,0:34:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,well.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.03,0:34:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Page two of four star rating,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.48,0:34:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,no rating, adjustable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.02,0:34:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I can focus on the star, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.86,0:34:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I can focus on the star rating
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.45,0:35:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,view, it's actually a view now.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.28,0:35:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If I go into my settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.77,0:35:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Settings, setting, Facebook
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.60,0:35:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,off.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.87,0:35:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'm finally actually reading
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.41,0:35:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,whether or not my setting is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.67,0:35:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,currently off or on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.21,0:35:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there are a couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.87,0:35:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,problems that we found during
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.57,0:35:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,our audit that we still haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.63,0:35:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,actually fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.03,0:35:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have no way of bringing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.62,0:35:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,up the delete sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.97,0:35:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no way of actually
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.33,0:35:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,changing the value of the star
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.56,0:35:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,rating view.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.54,0:35:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see what it is, I can see
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.05,0:35:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what the current number stars
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.19,0:35:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is, but I have no way of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.98,0:35:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,changing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.51,0:35:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I double tap on my
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.05,0:35:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,setting it's still not changing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.17,0:35:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that setting value.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.27,0:35:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the first thing I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.75,0:35:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,look at are custom actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.77,0:35:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to use these to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.15,0:35:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,bring up that delete sheet in
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.67,0:35:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,our sample app.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.00,0:35:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, a custom action is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.13,0:35:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,something that you add to an
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.00,0:36:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,element that is an action that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.32,0:36:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it has available to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.29,0:36:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, views have the property
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.87,0:36:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityCustomActions which
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.85,0:36:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you can override with an array
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.04,0:36:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of UI accessibilityCustomAction
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.34,0:36:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that are all of the actions
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.24,0:36:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,available to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.43,0:36:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does an action look
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.38,0:36:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,like?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.43,0:36:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well it has a name for instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.88,0:36:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,our delete action is called
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.27,0:36:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,delete because it tells the user
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.99,0:36:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what it does and it has a target
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.69,0:36:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and a selector that get called
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.15,0:36:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever that action is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.08,0:36:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,initiated.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.11,0:36:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when a view has custom
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.35,0:36:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,actions it's going to tell that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.61,0:36:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to the user and then the user
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.18,0:36:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,can swipe up or down with their
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.61,0:36:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,finger to cycle through the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.84,0:36:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,current actions of that element.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.00,0:36:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they land on the one
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.02,0:36:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that they want to activate a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.54,0:36:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,double tap instead of doing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.25,0:36:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever the default behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.28,0:36:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,will do will initiate that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.11,0:36:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,action.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.63,0:36:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance, with our
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.63,0:37:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,delete we can create a custom
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.05,0:37:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,action called delete, set our
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.11,0:37:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,self as the target with our
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.05,0:37:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,delete cell action method that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.54,0:37:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,returns a Boolean and that calls
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.05,0:37:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the code for actually initiating
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.30,0:37:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the delete of the cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.35,0:37:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,On our cell, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.84,0:37:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,override
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.44,0:37:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityCustomActions to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.61,0:37:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,contain this custom action.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.63,0:37:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now because we're overriding it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.96,0:37:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,on the cell and the cell itself
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.87,0:37:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't an accessibilityElement,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.36,0:37:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,all of its sub elements are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.28,0:37:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,All of its sub elements are
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.62,0:37:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,going to inherit the custom
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.25,0:37:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,actions of its parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.17,0:37:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I can actually initiate this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.20,0:37:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,delete action from any of the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.96,0:37:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,views on the cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.95,0:37:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have the default
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.41,0:37:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,activation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.30,0:37:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what if we want to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.95,0:37:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,override what the default
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.49,0:37:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior is when a VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.52,0:37:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,user double taps on an element.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.36,0:37:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.63,0:37:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,use to fix the problem of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.19,0:37:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,actually changing our settings.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.76,0:37:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What you can do is override
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.69,0:37:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityActivate, which
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.00,0:38:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,returns a Boolean indicating
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.34,0:38:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,whether or not the activation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.81,0:38:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,was successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.84,0:38:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example with our switch
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.96,0:38:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,cells we can override
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.23,0:38:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityActivate and set
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.63,0:38:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,whether or not the switch is on
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.74,0:38:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,based on its current on value.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.55,0:38:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're always going to return
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.18,0:38:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,true because we know that that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.81,0:38:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,action is always going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.10,0:38:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.13,0:38:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have adjustable
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.45,0:38:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,elements, so our star rating is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.29,0:38:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,adjustable and VoiceOver has a
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.67,0:38:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,mechanism for adjustable
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.08,0:38:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,elements to respond to increment
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.89,0:38:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and decrement calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.39,0:38:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the first thing we want to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.96,0:38:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,return in that element's traits
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.87,0:38:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is an adjustable element
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.44,0:38:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and that tells VoiceOver that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.30,0:38:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,element is going to respond to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.06,0:38:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the accessibilityIncrement and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.16,0:38:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,decrement calls which we can
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.97,0:38:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,override to do whatever behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.05,0:38:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we need when we increment and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.54,0:38:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,decrement.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.98,0:39:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And a user adjusts an adjustable
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.49,0:39:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,element by swiping up and down
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.17,0:39:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,with their finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.06,0:39:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Up as an increment, down as a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.34,0:39:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,decrement.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.29,0:39:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with our star's view we have
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.13,0:39:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of stars that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.71,0:39:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever it's set has code that
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.95,0:39:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,actually adjusts the view
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.21,0:39:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.02,0:39:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In its traits, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.52,0:39:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,include the adjustable trait.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.83,0:39:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And in increment we're simply
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.85,0:39:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,going to increase the number of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.91,0:39:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,stars by one and in decrement
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.19,0:39:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to decrease the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.44,0:39:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,number of stars by one and now
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.16,0:39:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that element is fully accessible
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.14,0:39:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to our VoiceOver users.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.21,0:39:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'd like to look at a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.18,0:39:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,different problem that we didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.42,0:39:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,see in our sample app.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.89,0:39:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, VoiceOver has this concept
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.50,0:39:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of pass-through which happens
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.98,0:39:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when a VoiceOver user double
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.38,0:39:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,taps and holds their finger and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.57,0:39:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it passes through the panning
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.85,0:39:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,gesture so I can actually run my
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.99,0:39:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,finger across the screen and get
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.63,0:40:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,a more fine adjustment of a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.02,0:40:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,slider like you see in this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.00,0:40:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,photo's page here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.53,0:40:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But we want a way to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.72,0:40:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver where it should
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.97,0:40:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,actually focus that panning when
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.63,0:40:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I initiate it because if I'm a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.80,0:40:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver user then I probably
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.11,0:40:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,am not going to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.15,0:40:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,accurately land my finger on
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.38,0:40:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that little sliding nub in the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.35,0:40:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,center right, I don't actually
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.80,0:40:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.95,0:40:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to use
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.80,0:40:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityActivationPoint
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.03,0:40:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the point that tells
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.73,0:40:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver when a pass-through
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.11,0:40:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs, what part of the UI do
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.67,0:40:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you actually want to hook into.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.95,0:40:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance, if we have our
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.46,0:40:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,slider view where we have some
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.99,0:40:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of slider nub then we can
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.34,0:40:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,override
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.03,0:40:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityActivationPoint to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.02,0:40:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,be the center of that nub so
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.63,0:40:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that whenever the user passes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.97,0:40:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,through that gesture it will
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.20,0:40:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,hook into the center of the nub
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.64,0:40:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and start sliding there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.87,0:41:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we have custom scrolling,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.27,0:41:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so you may have views that have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.51,0:41:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,swipe gestures on them that you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.94,0:41:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,can use to get to different
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.93,0:41:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,parts of the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.62,0:41:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, in photos if I
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.60,0:41:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,swipe up then I get to my
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.17,0:41:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,details.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.66,0:41:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a way that we can
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.55,0:41:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,get this behavior for VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.87,0:41:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,users as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.14,0:41:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called an
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.07,0:41:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityScroll, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.83,0:41:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,initiated by scrolling with
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.30,0:41:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,three fingers when VoiceOver is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.30,0:41:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.32,0:41:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And it returns a Boolean to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.62,0:41:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,indicate whether or not the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.18,0:41:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll was successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.68,0:41:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And it passes through a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.95,0:41:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,direction so that you can change
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.22,0:41:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the behavior based on what
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.23,0:41:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,direction the user is scrolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.74,0:41:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example with our image
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.19,0:41:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,view if we wanted to show
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.68,0:41:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,details like we do in the Photos
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.00,0:41:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,app we'd have some property that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.11,0:41:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,tells us whether or not we can
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.28,0:41:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,currently show the details and
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.95,0:41:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we have code that actually goes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.29,0:41:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,through and shows those details.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.14,0:42:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, what we're going to do
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.88,0:42:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is override accessibilityScroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.44,0:42:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to check can we show
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.97,0:42:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,our details and are we scrolling
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.68,0:42:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,in the right position or
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.10,0:42:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.34,0:42:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we do we're going to show
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.17,0:42:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,our details and return true,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.95,0:42:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise we're going to return
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.72,0:42:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,false.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.50,0:42:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I return false
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.62,0:42:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,VoiceOver is going to make a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.13,0:42:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,bonking noise to indicate to the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.93,0:42:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,user that whatever swipe that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.37,0:42:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,they just did was not a valid
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.70,0:42:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,swipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.84,0:42:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm not going to go through
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.17,0:42:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,actually adding all those things
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.67,0:42:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,into our sample app, but they
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.42,0:42:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,are in the finished version of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.81,0:42:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the sample which you can find
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.61,0:42:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and download at this URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.14,0:42:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And I recommend that you go and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.21,0:42:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,check it out and see how that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.98,0:42:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,code is implemented and see how
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.54,0:42:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it works in action, play around
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.96,0:42:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.42,0:42:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, I'd like to spend a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.51,0:42:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit of time talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.42,0:42:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Drag-and-Drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.30,0:43:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for those of you that missed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.26,0:43:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it at the keynote we unveiled
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.77,0:43:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Drag-and-Drop finally coming to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.35,0:43:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS where I can drag pieces of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.42,0:43:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,content and drop it in other
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.15,0:43:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,places in the interface.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.59,0:43:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, if I have photos
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.13,0:43:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,open next to notes I can drag a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.26,0:43:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,photo and drop it into one of my
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.66,0:43:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.25,0:43:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Now because this was just
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.38,0:43:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,unveiled two days ago I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.49,0:43:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,really expect all of you to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.11,0:43:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,already understand how that API
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.88,0:43:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,works.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.68,0:43:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are just two key
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.14,0:43:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,concepts that you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.46,0:43:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,understand before I talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.77,0:43:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the accessibility and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.34,0:43:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,drag sources and drop points.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.30,0:43:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, drag sources are all the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.27,0:43:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,points on my view that I can
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.19,0:43:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,initiate a drag from and drop
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.48,0:43:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,points conversely are all the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.90,0:43:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,places on my view that I can
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.42,0:43:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,drop content.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.89,0:43:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance, on the Home
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.08,0:43:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,screen which now uses
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.69,0:43:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Drag-and-Drop for rearranging
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.12,0:44:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,icons I have three drop points
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.63,0:44:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for each app when I'm moving
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.03,0:44:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,another.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.98,0:44:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is the left drop point
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.58,0:44:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which allows me to drop the app
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.73,0:44:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm currently moving to the left
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.94,0:44:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and shift everything else to the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.98,0:44:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.29,0:44:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the center drop point
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.31,0:44:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that will create a folder
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.02,0:44:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,between the two apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.34,0:44:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have the right drop point
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.85,0:44:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that will drop my current app to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.26,0:44:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.24,0:44:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And we need a way of describing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.47,0:44:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,those different drag sources and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.38,0:44:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,drop points to our VoiceOver
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.14,0:44:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.89,0:44:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.85,0:44:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,use this new API
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.20,0:44:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityDrag
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.40,0:44:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,SourcesDescriptors and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.88,0:44:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,accessibilityDrop
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.27,0:44:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,PointDescriptors.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.79,0:44:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They're arrays of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.96,0:44:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,UIAccessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.97,0:44:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,LocationDescriptor that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.68,0:44:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,described the drags and the
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.14,0:44:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,drops for review.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.11,0:44:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we create a UIAccessibility
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.28,0:44:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,LocationDescriptor for each
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.20,0:44:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,drag-and-drop.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.60,0:45:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The view is going to be the view
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.97,0:45:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that has the drag or drop
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.92,0:45:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,interaction associated with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.01,0:45:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The point is the point where the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.58,0:45:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,drag is initiated from or the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.88,0:45:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,drop is associated with.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.72,0:45:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the name is meant to
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.86,0:45:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,describe what that drag or drop
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.28,0:45:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,does.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.12,0:45:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's even an attributed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.49,0:45:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,name where you can use all those
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.58,0:45:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,attributed keys that I was
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.72,0:45:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,referring to earlier to tweak
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.55,0:45:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the way that VoiceOver describes
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.56,0:45:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the name of the descriptor.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.81,0:45:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's take a look at how
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.03,0:45:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this works in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.01,0:45:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is just a hypothetical
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.18,0:45:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,example this isn't an actually
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.35,0:45:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,springboard code.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.86,0:45:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's say that I was
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.02,0:45:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,implementing rearranging apps
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.04,0:45:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have a method that returns
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.12,0:45:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an app view for a given index
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.52,0:45:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,path.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.10,0:45:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well I'm going to start by
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.03,0:45:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,initializing that app view and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.93,0:45:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'm going to create a drag
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.82,0:45:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,descriptor and I'm going to give
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.70,0:45:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it the name drag whatever the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.09,0:45:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,app name is because that's what
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.45,0:45:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.46,0:45:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the center of where the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.12,0:46:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,app is dragged from or sorry the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.87,0:46:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,point where the app is dragged
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.80,0:46:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,from is its center.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.03,0:46:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the view that actually has
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.50,0:46:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that drag interaction is myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.81,0:46:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'm going to override the
